{"votes": {"funny": 0, "useful": 0, "cool": 0}, "user_id": "HaqStKX7oqpx5ymDHE58Ow", "review_id": "FA0ZLaIo7PJak-6XxNEMUg", "text": "i came here for a late lunch, around 2 pm on a friday, with some girlfriends. we were waiting for the last of our party of four to arrive for about 10 minutes, and got asked no less than 5 times if we were ready to sit, and then once we succumbed to that, if we were ready to order. mind you, we were the only people in the restaurant besides one lone guy. the food was good, with some unusual choices on the rather extensive menu. i got a toasted burrito stuffed with chorizo, mashed potatoes, jalapenos, red beans, and spicy cheddar cheese, with onion rings on the side. it was hearty and delicious, with a nice kick. to wash it down, a nice tall glass of red sangria did the trick. the sangria tasted nice, but there was not even one piece of fruit in it. after reading some of these other reviews, i wish i had ordered something with toast! this is a good, solid diner, especially in the boston area, where diners are severely lacking. the service needs to be worked on though: our waitress was completely hot and cold (in our faces one second and nowhere to be found the next). the food came pretty quickly though, and we were all satisfied with our meals.", "business_id": "yx4IYpg9MGbrVqNdZwXX_A", "stars": 3, "date": "2009-07-28", "type": "review"}